summary: An ordinance repealing Ordinance No. 25012 entitled: "An ordinance providing for the condemnation, appropriation, taking and damaging of that portion of East Spring Street lying east of Lakeside Avenue which was vacated by Ordinance No. 20925 and Ordinance No. 21388, all in the City of Seattle,, for park, drive and boulevard purposes; and providing that payment for cost of said condemnation be made from the Park Fund of the City of Seattle" approved September 9, 1910, directing the Corporation Counsel to dismiss Cause No. 76962 in the Superior Court; instituted under said ordinance, and providing for the payment of costs.
